<|startoftext|>Dish: zigzag glazed green bean and couscous cakes
Directions: in a large saucepan , over medium heat , cook the onion , celery and garlic until just tender , about 5 minutes
stir in the green beans , sugar , tomatoes , tomato paste , thyme , bay leaves , and dried oregano
bring to a simmer over medium heat , then lower the heat to maintain a simmer while making the casserole: in a large bowl , mix the flour , baking powder , baking soda and salt together
add the oil and milk alternately if the mixture is large
beat the egg yolks with a wooden spoon until stiff
add the milk mixture in one steady stream , being sure to scrape the bowl with a rubber spatula
add the butter and beat until the butter is incorporated
reduce the heat to medium-low and continue to beat the egg whites until stiff , about 2 minutes
set aside to cool
heat oil in a large heavy skillet over medium-high heat
add the onion and cook , stirring , until tender , 20 to 25 minutes
add the drained green beans and fry , stirring , until tender , 20 to 25 minutes
add the chicken broth , cornstarch , and baking powder
mix well
boil the cup sauce , stirring the mixture with a ladle , until it reduces to 1 cup
stir in the cup sauce , 1 tablespoon at a time , until this mixture begins boiling
add the cooled zigzag glazed green beans and couscous and cook for 3 to 5 minutes , stirring well every once in awhile
cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 10 minutes
before serving , sprinkle with additional butter and powdered sugar
best served cold
can also be made 1 day ahead of time'<|endoftext|>
